I show someone I am minstering to that I genuinely care about them by genuinely caring about them.
I show someone I am minstering to that I genuinely care about them by not only being there for them, since that's not really enough sometimes, but also by lifting them up when they fall in deep and violent waves.
I show someone I am minstering to that I genuinely care about them by maintaining the eternal perspective needed to guide us to receive helpful revelation on how to serve my ministering people.
I show someone I am minstering to that I genuinely care about them by persisting in our help for them, even if they do not get it at first.
